What is the role of a quantative analyst?
(1) Improving the trading architecture used to place trades;
(2) Imporving the signals to evaluate trade ideas;
(3) Reducing transaction costs and/or market impact;
(4) Managing portfolio risk;
(5) Testing and deploying new trading strategies.

Day-to-day work of a Quant Analyst will always involve quantitative research in some form:
(1) Reading academic literature to help ground trading strategies in theory;
(2) Creating and testing a hypothesis for a given trading strategy;
(3) Back-testing the strategy with existing data on an out-of-sample basis using actual transaction costs;
(4) Programming and implementing the traidng strategy and proposing a systematic method for increasing 
    or decreasing portfolio risk.
